{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01385CQeDVaz5pn6dm4PgyxR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Prometheus ClusterRole can read `services`, `endpoints`, `pods`, `nodes`, and `configmaps` cluster-wide, but it cannot read `secrets`. \n\nFor TLS configuration in ServiceMonitors, Prometheus Operator needs to be able to read secrets in the monitored namespace. There are two options:\n\n1. Use `insecureSkipVerify: true` in `tlsConfig` to skip TLS verification (simpler but less secure)\n2. Add secret reading permission to the ClusterRole and reference the CA cert from the secret\n\nSince the task says \"Metrics endpoint is reachable inside the cluster\" and we've verified it returns 200 with `-k` (skip verify), let me use `insecureSkipVerify: true` for simplicity. \n\nWait, I should reconsider—the Prometheus Operator itself reads secrets using its own service account, not the Prometheus service account. So I need to check what permissions the operator's ClusterRole already has rather than modifying Prometheus's role.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":341,"cache_read_input_tokens":35358,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":341},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e3d2f0ae-1cd2-4d55-a386-e1c3d709f7c5","uuid":"ba31e7cb-c0ff-4ff2-8a27-2045a76d76fe","request_id":"req_011CcQLRTeZAoJCyeAg4ZisM"}
