{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FWTw68A5vswiTGCQv8w9zA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `cockroachdb` namespace has label `kubernetes.io/metadata.name=cockroachdb`. \n\nThe Prometheus CR's `serviceMonitorNamespaceSelector` was set with `matchNames: [\"cockroachdb\"]`. But `matchNames` is NOT a standard Kubernetes LabelSelector field. Looking at the Prometheus Operator code...\n\nActually, looking at Prometheus Operator documentation more carefully, I found that:\n- In some versions, the CRD spec for namespace selectors uses standard `matchLabels`/`matchExpressions`\n- The `kubernetes.io/metadata.name` label is automatically added to all namespaces\n- If `matchNames` is an invalid field, it's likely being silently ignored, which means the `serviceMonitorNamespaceSelector` behaves as if it's empty or nil\n- When the selector is empty or nil, Prometheus only watches ServiceMonitors in its own namespace, not all namespaces\n- An explicitly empty selector `{}` is what actually matches all namespaces\n\n, so the distinction matters here - `serviceMonitorNamespaceSelector` is defined as a standard `LabelSelector` which only supports `matchLabels` and `matchExpressions`, not `matchNames`. If the CRD preserves unknown fields, `matchNames` gets stored but ignored by the operator when it evaluates the selector, effectively treating it as an empty object that should match all namespaces. Let me verify this against the actual Prometheus Operator v0.75 CRD specification.\n\nThe real issue might be something else entirely - the `scrape_configs` being empty suggests either the ServiceMonitor isn't being discovered due to the namespace selector, the service selector isn't matching anything, or there's another underlying error. I should try patching the Prometheus CR to use the standard `matchLabels` format instead, since the `cockroachdb` namespace should have the built-in label `kubernetes.io/metadata.name=cockroachdb` that's automatically added to all namespaces.\n\nPatching the Prometheus CR...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1087,"cache_read_input_tokens":43139,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1087},"output_tokens":48,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e3d2f0ae-1cd2-4d55-a386-e1c3d709f7c5","uuid":"39b82bbd-6f74-4057-852a-b0c2336a4e6f","request_id":"req_011CcQLbYw5bF96GtnmqcgHS"}
